      • valueOf

        public static AbstractTextType<?> valueOf​(String string)
                                   throws IllegalArgumentException
        Create an instance from String.

        Note: The implementation at abstract level forces subclasses to fulfill the ValueOfContractor marker. If a subclass does not hide this method, a MustImplementError is thrown.

        Parameters:
        string - The string to create from.
        Returns:
        The created instance or null, iff the given string is null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given string does not match basic criteria for being a language abbreviation.
        Since:
        5.2.210803
